<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$b">
   <head>Scope and Content</head>
   <p>Mozambique General Subject Files contain information on the Mozambique Marxist government, including President Samora Machel, elections, and resistance. Additionally, there are documents pertaining to Mozambique’s international relations with nations such as Portugal, the Soviet Union,
South Africa, Zimbabwe and other African nations.</p>
   <p>Documents pertaining to issues of religion highlight the oppression of the Catholic and Anglican churches, Machel’s “war on the church,” external pressure for freedom of religion, and missionary activities. There are individual folders for the following denominations: Anglican, Islam,
Lutheran, and Roman Catholic.</p>
</scopecontent>
